snippet.textDisplay: There are many things that can be said about the DC movies, and the overall state of DCEU but there is actually one thing that needs to be said [And I really hate this opinion to the level of "war" between DC and Marvel] - this crossover brought much needed good will because it ACTUALLY WAS A CROSSOVER. Marvel's Endgame was a historical event but it lacked one serious thing - actual "gathering" of the heroes. We all wanted to see Daredevil running among the army in the final battle against Thanos, we all wanted to see Fitz and Simmons helping to recreate the gauntlet, to have Coulson back, etc. Ezra's cameo might've been brief and it won't influence the movies whatsoever but it's monumental in the grand scheme of things - DC pulled some strings, got Ezra on board, gave him the Flash costume and got him on board of a TV SHOW. Marvel dumped it's TV characters that had massive potential focused on one thing - I'm not saying that it's a bad thing for them as a company, but I think all of us would've screamed with Glee if we'd see TV characters in Endgame.

snippet.textDisplay: I loved all the other CW crossovers, but man... was this some of the dumbest tv I've ever seen.  I can't even begin a list of complaints and things done poorly, who has that kinda time?  But fuck me.. "Oliver Queen, I am Jim Corrigan, but I am also the Spectre.  Now it is your turn."  Jesus Christ.  That might be the most ham fisted character intro in history.  The Smallville & especially the Kevin Conroy stuff was terrible, but one good thing they did was mock and then erase the Birds of Prey TV show from history.
snippet.textOriginal: I loved all the other CW crossovers, but man... was this some of the dumbest tv I've ever seen.  I can't even begin a list of complaints and things done poorly, who has that kinda time?  But fuck me.. "Oliver Queen, I am Jim Corrigan, but I am also the Spectre.  Now it is your turn."
